			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm sorry but to say fatalities due to intoxication would double if marijuana was legal is all kinds of wrong.  As he said people that are high tend to drive slower, why?  Because pot INCREASES awareness.  Couple that with the light paranoia accompanying the high (omg there might be a cop behind that building) and it becomes infinitely safer than driving drunk.  Or hell even just being drunk period.  Drunk = violent for alot of people.  Stoned = hey maaaaan mellow out there.  Not saying there are no potheads out there that dont start shit up, nor am I saying there are no accidents because of it.  Some people cant handle it.  And being a *choke* gateway drug?  Alcohol leads far more people to the euphoria they seek, pot is the easiest to come by of the illegals, and thus shoulders the blame (more propaganda).
<br />

<br />
I say this from experience, tho i dont currently smoke i was a chronic user til about a year ago,  I actually drive better high.  I would be able to see everything ahead and behind me. quickly notice and react to a sudden lane change, see that old lady pulling out of the grocery store, etc.  The only danger i can conceive is having some of your favorite music playing during the drive, because music takes ahold of you more so than ever in that state.  Like Tool....mmmm tool.<br />_________________<br />Pancakes -some monk
