			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I'm sorry but to say fatalities due to intoxication would double if marijuana was legal is all kinds of wrong. As he said people that are high tend to drive slower, why? Because pot INCREASES awareness. Couple that with the light paranoia accompanying the high (omg there might be a cop behind that building) and it becomes infinitely safer than driving drunk. Or hell even just being drunk period. Drunk = violent for alot of people. Stoned = hey maaaaan mellow out there. Not saying there are no potheads out there that dont start shit up, nor am I saying there are no accidents because of it. Some people cant handle it. And being a *choke* gateway drug? Alcohol leads far more people to the euphoria they seek, pot is the easiest to come by of the illegals, and thus shoulders the blame (more propaganda). </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I agree with you the estimate of the driving fatalaties is wrong.  The estimate is probably far too low in terms of its likely increase.  While it's true from my observations that people high on pot do tend drive slower -- it doesn't mean they don't do stupid manuevuers or be twitchy drivers ("OMG, a cat! *swerve into other lane of traffic and the car that was passing, etc*).  
<br />

<br />
As for the view that pot increases awareness, that is absurd.   Yes, it can make one paranoid (due to the legal implications) but that hardly means they are being more observant than normal.  They are probably more alert than a person drunk on alcohol to the same amount, but we've already touched on why.    
<br />

<br />
And whether you like to admit it to yourself or not; pot 'is' a gateway drug.  So is alcohol technically.  Both depress inhibitions and make the user morelikely to 'experiment' with other things.  And that's if the person who handed out the pot is nice; it's much harder for a bartender to lace my drink with a narcotic than it is a dealer.  Impossible?  No, but atmosphere, regulations and many other factors make such things extremely unlikely.  gateway simply refers to the fact that it's viewed as trivial and opens the door for 'real' drugs.  the fact that pot is illegal only mkes it even more likely the people who have it will also have speed, xtc, etc. 
<br />

<br />
The key is as Jeal alluded to: the pot being smoked today is nothing like what your parents smoked.  Unless you're 8 or so years old, and even then I'd say it's unlikely.  I'm told I'm genetically predisposed to get addicted to stimulant drugs; but frankly I still view that as a crock. We all are.    Frankly, I don't smoke pot; have I tried it?  Not tellin'.   But, I also don't drink much.  I figured out many years ago that most people drink or do drugs to act like i do when I'm sober; so it kinda defeats the purpose if I want to be social and fit-in.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_lol.gif" alt="Laughing" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Personally, I do think it should be legalilzed; and not just 'pot' but most of the drugs.  I seriously doubt after the inital suge in use the first couple of years it would be any higher than it is now.  Give people places where they can use it and not only would the prices drop for those who want to use it; but the black market for it would crumble.  They can't compete with pharmaceutical companies.  
<br />

<br />
I'm not suggesting that use of it on a job would not be punishable by any means.  Just as people can get fired for showingup drunk, so they shold be for showing up stoned/etc.  Product would be safer and availible.  Those prone to overdosing would get it out of the way and possibly be in an area where they could get help if needed/wanted.  But, most importantly, a lot of criminals would have to find new venues for profit.  Hell, the black market makes TONS of money, LETS TAX IT and reduce taxes on wages!  <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
-Merilee</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
